javadoc:
This interface represents a collection of AddressSets (actually AddressSetViews). 
  It defines a set of methods that can efficiently be performed on a collection
  of one or more AddressSets.

methods.javadoc:
Determine if any AddressSet in this collection intersects with the specified address set.
@param addrSet address set to check intersection with.
methods.name: intersects
methods.comment: Determine if any AddressSet in this collection intersects with the specified address set.

params.name: addrSet
params.comment: address set to check intersection with.

methods.name: intersects
methods.comment:
Determine if range specified by start and end intersects with any of the AddressSets
 in this collection.

return.comment: true if the given range intersects this address set collection.

methods.name: contains
methods.comment: Test if the address is contained within any of the addressSets in this collection.

return.comment: true if addr exists in the set, false otherwise.

methods.name: hasFewerRangesThan
methods.comment:
Tests whether this collection of addressSets has approximately fewer ranges than
 the given threshold. This is probably estimated by adding up the number of ranges
 in each AddressSet in this collections. Returns true if the total is less than the 
 given threshold.

params.name: rangeThreshold
params.comment: the number of ranges to test against.

return.comment: true if the max possible ranges is less than the given threshold.

methods.javadoc: Returns a single AddressSet containing the union of all the addressSetViews in the collection.
methods.name: getCombinedAddressSet
methods.comment: Returns a single AddressSet containing the union of all the addressSetViews in the collection.

methods.name: findFirstAddressInCommon
methods.comment: Finds the first address in this collection that is also in the given addressSet.

params.name: set
params.comment: the addressSet to search for the first (lowest) common address.

return.comment: the first address that is contained in this set and the given set.

methods.javadoc:
Returns true if all the AddressSets in this collection are empty.
@return true if all the AddressSets in this collection are empty.
methods.name: isEmpty
methods.comment: Returns true if all the AddressSets in this collection are empty.

return.comment: true if all the AddressSets in this collection are empty.

methods.javadoc:
Returns the smallest address in this collection or null if the collection is empty.
@return the smallest address in this collection or null if the collection is empty.
methods.name: getMinAddress
methods.comment: Returns the smallest address in this collection or null if the collection is empty.

return.comment: the smallest address in this collection or null if the collection is empty.

methods.javadoc:
Returns the largest address in this collection or null if the collection is empty.
@return the largest address in this collection or null if the collection is empty.
methods.name: getMaxAddress
methods.comment: Returns the largest address in this collection or null if the collection is empty.

return.comment: the largest address in this collection or null if the collection is empty.
